        "channel_id": "4r2k26zkdjnfm4dvg1e1hczscb",
        "title": "Apple Reports FY2024 Revenue of $391.0B with 46.2% Gross Margin",
        "body": "<p>Apple today reported <strong>revenue of $391.0 billion</strong> for the FY2024 period, with a <strong>gross margin of 46.2%</strong>. Operating income reached <strong>$123.2 billion</strong>, and net income stood at <strong>$93.7 billion</strong>. These figures reflect disciplined cost management and a continued focus on high-margin services, alongside robust product sales across iPhone, Mac, iPad, and wearables. The quarter saw <strong>shares repurchases of $95 billion</strong>, underscoring shareholder value creation.</p><p>Apple also highlighted a diversified product mix and ongoing investments in R&D, totaling approximately <strong>$29 billion</strong> in FY2024 to drive next-generation silicon, AI, and software platforms. The company maintains <strong>capital flexibility with <strong>$153.0B</strong> in cash and securities and <strong>$101.3B</strong> in debt.</p><p>CEO Tim Cook reaffirmed Apple\u2019s commitment to privacy, security, and user-centric design as core tenets of the business strategy. The results underscore Apple\u2019s ability to deliver premium experiences at scale, supported by a geographically diverse footprint, including offices in Cupertino, Austin, Seattle, New York, and London.</p><p>Read the full report at <a href=\"https://investor.apple.com\">investor.apple.com</a>.</p>",
        "status": "Published",
        "tags": [
